                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 3.  <span>Menin is required for both active and repressive histone modifications in AT1 cells.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec5.fig1.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec5.fig1.caption1.p1"></a><p>Menin excision (<em>Men1<sup>Δ/Δ</sup></em>) dramatically reduced active (A) and repressive (B) histone modifications.</p>
